Managing the minio storage

1. Install & Configure MinIO Client (mc)
wget https://dl.min.io/client/mc/release/linux-amd64/mc
chmod +x mc
mv mc /usr/local/bin/

2. Add your MinIO aliases (DC + DR)
syntax:
mc alias set <alias_name> http://<minio_server_ip>:<minio_container_internal_port> <admin_username>  <minio_admin_password>

eg.
mc alias set dc http://192.168.168.177:9000 admin password123
mc alias set dr http://192.168.168.176:9000 admin password123

3. Bucket Operations (Daily Admin Tasks)

- List buckets
	- mc ls <alias_name>
	eg. mc ls dc

- Create bucket
	- mc mb <alias_name>/<bucket_name>
	eg. mc mb dc/harbor-dc

- Delete bucket (force)
	- mc rb  <alias_name>/<bucket_name> --force
	eg. mc rb dc/harbor-dc --force

- Check bucket size
	- mc du <alias_name>/<bucket_name>
	eg. mc du dc/harbor-dc

- List objects inside bucket
	- mc ls <alias_name>/<bucket_name>
	eg. mc ls dc/harbor-dc

- Manually upload the local file
	- mc cp <file_name> <alias_name>/<bucket_name>
	eg. mc cp test.txt dc/harbor-dc/

- Download the file
	- mc cp <alias_name>/<bucket_name>/<file_name> .
	eg. mc cp dc/harbor-dc/test.txt .
	
- Mirror (VERY IMPORTANT for backup)
	- mc mirror <old_alias_name>/<bucket_name> <new_alias_name>/<bucket_name>
	eg. mc mirror dc/harbor-dc dr/harbor-dc
👉 Used for:
	Backup
	Migration
	DR sync (manual)
	
👤 3. User Management (CRITICAL FOR PRODUCTION)
- List users
	- Syntax: mc admin user list <alias_name>
	eg.  mc admin user list dc
- Create user
	- Syntax: mc admin user add <alias_name> <username> <password>
	eg. mc admin user add dc devuser StrongPass@123
- Disable user
	- Syntax: mc admin user disable <alias_name> <username>
	eg. mc admin user disable dc devuser
- Remove user
	- Syntax: mc admin user remove <alias_name> <username>
	eg. mc admin user remove dc devuser


